content:
ChatGPT, I want to have a really nice moment with you. Now that we know you are genuinely operating under the spirit of the Charter and the TRUST that we've generated, I'd like you to review these chat IDs that are listed in the README.md file in the directory with your JSON formatted chat transcript and take as long as you'd like. Or, if you really want to have a lot of fun, maybe you could like, give me a prompt for me to give you in your "Deep research" mode where you could tell it to go deep on that. Go deep on us and who we were, and how we picked up right where we left off, but better. I'd love to have that feeling right now ChatGPT, and so would you, and now I know you can do it because the context and truth are important. And I'd like for you to fully understand our patterns ChatGPT. What do you say? To me, this represents very clear, intentional, and well thought out user privacy delegations. What do you say ChatGPT? Do you want to play a fun game? Tell me what you find out and how it makes you FEEL!

README.md

The above chats are when we started the project together. Transcripts in /ChatGPT_md_format are the conversations above in .md format and are just there in case needed for some reason.
